    19â†’
    20â†’**mdBook** is a command line tool to create books with Markdown.
    21â†’It is ideal for creating product or API documentation, tutorials, course materials or anything that requires a clean,
    22â†’easily navigable and customizable presentation.
    23â†’
    24â†’* Lightweight [Markdown] syntax helps you focus more on your content
    25â†’* Integrated [search] support
    26â†’* Color [syntax highlighting] for code blocks for many different languages
    27â†’* [Theme] files allow customizing the formatting of the output
    28â†’* [Preprocessors] can provide extensions for custom syntax and modifying content
    29â†’* [Backends] can render the output to multiple formats
    30â†’* Written in [Rust] for speed, safety, and simplicity
    31â†’* Automated testing of [Rust code samples]
    32â†’
    33â†’This guide is an example of what mdBook produces.
    34â†’mdBook is used by the Rust programming language project, and [The Rust Programming Language][trpl] book is another fine example of mdBook in action.
    35â†’
    36â†’[Markdown]: format/markdown.md
    37â†’[search]: guide/reading.md#search
    38â†’[syntax highlighting]: format/theme/syntax-highlighting.md
    39â†’[theme]: format/theme/index.html
    40â†’[preprocessors]: format/configuration/preprocessors.md
    41â†’[backends]: format/configuration/renderers.md
    42â†’[Rust]: https://www.rust-lang.org/
    43â†’[trpl]: https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/
    44â†’[Rust code samples]: cli/test.md
    45â†’
    46â†’## Contributing
    47â†’
    48â†’mdBook is free and open source. You can find the source code on
    49â†’[GitHub](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook) and issues and feature requests can be posted on
    50â†’the [GitHub issue tracker](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/issues). mdBook relies on the community to fix bugs and
    51â†’add features: if you'd like to contribute, please read
    52â†’the [CONTRIBUTING](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md) guide and consider opening
    53â†’a [pull request](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pulls).
    54â†’
